{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:sirach.27",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 27 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:1",
      "text": "Many have sinned for a small matter; and he that seeketh for abundance will turn his eyes away.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:2",
      "text": "As a nail sticketh fast between the joinings of the stones; so doth sin stick close between buying and selling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:3",
      "text": "Unless a man hold himself diligently in the fear of the Lord, his house shall soon be overthrown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:4",
      "text": "As when one sifteth with a sieve, the refuse remaineth; so the filth of man in his talk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:5",
      "text": "The furnace proveth the potter's vessels; so the trial of man is in his reasoning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:6",
      "text": "The fruit declareth if the tree have been dressed; so is the utterance of a conceit in the heart of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:7",
      "text": "Praise no man before thou hearest him speak; for this is the trial of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:8",
      "text": "If thou followest righteousness, thou shalt obtain her, and put her on, as a glorious long robe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:9",
      "text": "The birds will resort unto their like; so will truth return unto them that practise in her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:10",
      "text": "As the lion lieth in wait for the prey; so sin for them that work iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:11",
      "text": "The discourse of a godly man is always with wisdom; but a fool changeth as the moon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:12",
      "text": "If thou be among the indiscreet, observe the time; but be continually among men of understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:13",
      "text": "The discourse of fools is irksome, and their sport is the wantonness of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:14",
      "text": "The talk of him that sweareth much maketh the hair stand upright; and their brawls make one stop his ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:15",
      "text": "The strife of the proud is bloodshedding, and their revilings are grievous to the ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:16",
      "text": "Whoso discovereth secrets loseth his credit; and shall never find friend to his mind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:17",
      "text": "Love thy friend, and be faithful unto him: but if thou betrayest his secrets, follow no more after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:18",
      "text": "For as a man hath destroyed his enemy; so hast thou lost the love of thy neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:19",
      "text": "As one that letteth a bird go out of his hand, so hast thou let thy neighbour go, and shalt not get him again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:20",
      "text": "Follow after him no more, for he is too far off; he is as a roe escaped out of the snare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:21",
      "text": "As for a wound, it may be bound up; and after reviling there may be reconcilement: but he that betrayeth secrets is without hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:22",
      "text": "He that winketh with the eyes worketh evil: and he that knoweth him will depart from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:23",
      "text": "When thou art present, he will speak sweetly, and will admire thy words: but at the last he will writhe his mouth, and slander thy sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:24",
      "text": "I have hated many things, but nothing like him; for the Lord will hate him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:25",
      "text": "Whoso casteth a stone on high casteth it on his own head; and a deceitful stroke shall make wounds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:26",
      "text": "Whoso diggeth a pit shall fall therein: and he that setteth a trap shall be taken therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:27",
      "text": "He that worketh mischief, it shall fall upon him, and he shall not know whence it cometh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:28",
      "text": "Mockery and reproach are from the proud; but vengeance, as a lion, shall lie in wait for him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:29",
      "text": "They that rejoice at the fall of the righteous shall be taken in the snare; and anguish shall consume them before they die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.27.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:30",
      "text": "Malice and wrath, even these are abominations; and the sinful man shall have them both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
